      "blocks": {
        "heading_QW44cT": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "title": "FAQ"
          }
        },
        "question_LqfH3K": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "default_open": false,
            "title": "What are droptail cargo bib shorts used for?",
            "content": "<p>The cargo pockets spread your essentials across the bibs instead of overloading jersey pockets. Two on each leg improve weight distribution and let you ride with just a tee when you want to skip the jersey entirely.</p>",
            "show_icon": false,
            "icon_name": "icon-award",
            "icon_size": 20,
            "icon_color": ""
          }
        },
        "question_j4yhLn": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "default_open": false,
            "title": "How do Ornot droptail cargo bib shorts fit?",
            "content": "<p>Our Droptail Cargo Bib Shorts feature a performance fit with moderate compression. They are supportive enough for long rides without the restrictive feel of race bibs. They’re nice for short rides, too. If you're between sizes, size down for a more compressive fit. It will keep the pad in place better and give you a more comfortable ride.</p>",
            "show_icon": false,
            "icon_name": "icon-award",
            "icon_size": 20,
            "icon_color": ""
          }
        },
        "question_pjLqd3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "default_open": false,
            "title": "Are droptail cargo bib shorts good for gravel riding?",
            "content": "<p>Yes. The added pockets make it easy to carry food and essentials, while the supportive fit and durable fabrics are well suited to long gravel rides and mixed terrain. Pssst - they work great on the road, too.</p>",
            "show_icon": false,
            "icon_name": "icon-award",
            "icon_size": 20,
            "icon_color": ""
          }
        },
        "question_MBpLid": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "default_open": false,
            "title": "why droptail cargo bib shorts over bike shorts?",
            "content": "<p>Bib shorts use shoulder straps instead of a waistband, which keeps everything in place while you ride and avoids that tight feeling around your midsection. The fit stays more stable, the chamois doesn’t shift around, and pressure is spread more evenly over long days in the saddle. They also tend to breathe better up top, which is why most riders end up reaching for bib shorts when comfort really matters.</p>",
            "show_icon": false,
            "icon_name": "icon-award",
            "icon_size": 20,
            "icon_color": ""
          }
        },
        "question_a3paL4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "default_open": false,
            "title": "What makes Ornot droptail Cargo Bib Shorts comfortable for long rides?",
            "content": "<p>Our droptail Cargo Bib Shorts are designed for all-day comfort, with a high-density Women's chamois, compressive fabrics, and pockets that keep your snacks secure. The result is a bib that performs on long road rides, gravel routes, and everything in between.</p>",
            "show_icon": false,
            "icon_name": "icon-award",
            "icon_size": 20,
            "icon_color": ""
          }
        }
      },
